    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 28.22,
      "end": 29.98,
      "text": "Recorded by Lee Dunkelberg.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 31.6,
      "end": 39.22,
      "text": "A wagoneer was driving his team along a muddy lane with a full load behind them.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 39.84,
      "end": 48.22,
      "text": "When the wheels of his wagon sank so deep in the mire that no efforts of his horses could",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 48.22,
      "end": 48.72,
      "text": "move them.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 49.76,
      "end": 58.54,
      "text": "As he stood there, looking helplessly on, and calling loudly at intervals upon Hercules",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 58.54,
      "end": 67.06,
      "text": "for assistance, the God himself appeared and said to him,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 67.78,
      "end": 73.34,
      "text": "But you were shoulder to the wheel, man, and goat on your horses,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 74.2,
      "end": 79.14,
      "text": "and then you may call on Hercules to assist you.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 79.14,
      "end": 90.24,
      "text": "If you won't lift a finger to help yourself, you can't expect Hercules or anyone else to come to your raid.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 92.0,
      "end": 94.48,
      "text": "Heaven helps those who help themselves.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 95.82,
      "end": 99.52,
      "text": "End of Hercules and the Wagoneer.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
